      "name": "Mesh convergence study — centrifugal pump hemolysis CFD",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation applied to three mesh densities (coarse 4.1M, medium 9.8M, fine 22.3M cells) for the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI at design-point conditions (6 L/min, 3500 RPM) is 3.2%, within the MRL 5 acceptance criterion of ≤5% GCI.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-04-19T14:22:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-piv-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — FDA pump benchmark",
      "description": "Computational velocity fields compared against FDA-published particle image velocimetry (PIV) data for the generic centrifugal pump. Mean absolute error in axial velocity across 312 measurement points is 4.7 cm/s (8.1% of peak velocity). Shear stress distribution shows qualitative agreement with experimental hot-film measurements; 94% of predicted shear stress values fall within ±15% of experimental bounds.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-04-19T14:29:47Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-experimental",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index experimental correlation — Morrison 2022 dataset",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro measurements from Morrison et al. (2022) across 5 operating points. Pearson correlation r=0.91; mean relative error 11.4%. Prediction interval coverage at 95% confidence: 4 of 5 operating points within bounds. Systematic over-prediction of 8% at high-speed low-flow condition attributed to secondary flow recirculation not fully resolved at MRL 5 mesh density.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-04-19T14:18:33Z"
    }
